<subSubSection id="C3776556ED733817FC9AFDCFFA98FDFC" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED733817FC9AFDCFFA98FDFC" blockId="546.[810,1452,275,2070]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FC9AFDCFFC25FDDA" bold="true" box="[863,992,513,539]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name alludes to the dorsoventrally depressed body of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED733811FC9AFD8BFEBBFC50" lastPageId="548" lastPageNumber="549" pageId="546" pageNumber="547" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED733817FC9AFD8BFB8AFBDB" blockId="546.[810,1452,275,2070]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED733817FC9AFD8BFB9FFD9E" bold="true" box="[863,1114,581,607]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FB75FD8BFAFAFDA1" box="[1200,1343,581,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 365" captionStartId="547.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[210,1347,211,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@547.[193,1394,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="547" captionText="FIGURE 365. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus, ventral; C, urosome, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxilla; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.1 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592044/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 365A, B</figureCitation>
) swollen, 1.94 mm long. Prosome curved ventrally, depressed, makedly broaderposteriorly, 1.03 mm wide, and 0.79 mm dorsoventral depth. Cephalosome directed posteriorly; dorsal cephalic shield distinct, small in relation to metasome, lacking posterolateral processes. Metasome unsegmented, with 2 dorsal constrictions anteriorly; posterolateral part more expanded than anterior and middle regions; entire metasome forming brood pouch. Freeurosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FC17FCB9FB80FC53" box="[978,1093,887,914]" captionStart="FIGURE 365" captionStartId="547.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[210,1347,211,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@547.[193,1394,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="547" captionText="FIGURE 365. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus, ventral; C, urosome, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxilla; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.1 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592044/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 365C</figureCitation>
) short, slightly widerthan long, 5-segmented, but genital somite fused with metasome. Caudal rami fused with anal somite, without trace of articulation, strongly tapering, nearly as long as wide, setulose but lacking setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED733817FC9AFBECFB7FFA4E" blockId="546.[810,1452,275,2070]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FC1FFBEFFB9CFBFD" box="[986,1113,1057,1084]" captionStart="FIGURE 365" captionStartId="547.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[210,1347,211,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@547.[193,1394,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="547" captionText="FIGURE 365. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus, ventral; C, urosome, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxilla; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.1 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592044/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 365D</figureCitation>
) large, slightly wider than long, semicircular, with scattered setules. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FCF7FBABFC62FB41" box="[818,935,1125,1152]" captionStart="FIGURE 365" captionStartId="547.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[210,1347,211,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@547.[193,1394,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="547" captionText="FIGURE 365. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus, ventral; C, urosome, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxilla; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.1 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592044/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 365E</figureCitation>
) short, broad, 90 μm long, 1.5 times longer than wide, incompletely 5-segmented; articulations expressed only on posterior surface of appendage; few setae indistinguishable from scattered setules. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FCF7FB23FC61FAC9" box="[818,932,1261,1288]" captionStart="FIGURE 365" captionStartId="547.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[210,1347,211,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@547.[193,1394,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="547" captionText="FIGURE 365. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus, ventral; C, urosome, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxilla; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.1 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592044/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 365F</figureCitation>
) 3-segmented, consistingof coxa, basis, and unsegmentedendopod; coxaandbasisunarmed; endopod about 2.7 timeslongerthan wide (41×15 μm): armed with 5 setae (arranged as 1, 2, and 2) plus short terminal claw, aboutone-thirdaslongas endopod.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED733817FC9AFA59FCACF84F" blockId="546.[810,1452,275,2070]" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FC0CFA59FB85FA73" box="[969,1088,1431,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 365" captionStartId="547.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[210,1347,211,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@547.[193,1394,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="547" captionText="FIGURE 365. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus, ventral; C, urosome, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxilla; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.1 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592044/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 365G</figureCitation>
) semicircular, much widerthan long, unornamented. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FB64FA77FADFFA15" box="[1185,1306,1465,1492]" captionStart="FIGURE 365" captionStartId="547.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[210,1347,211,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@547.[193,1394,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="547" captionText="FIGURE 365. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus, ventral; C, urosome, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxilla; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.1 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592044/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 365H</figureCitation>
) with broad coxal gnathobase bearing 4 teeth; proximal second tooth smaller: basiswith 1 seta medially; exopod with 5 setae; proportional lengths of setae 12:13:15:16:10 from inner to outer; endopod with 1 broad seta on first segment and 4 (2 medial and 2 distal) subequal setae on second. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FC6DF94BFBD1F961" box="[936,1044,1669,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 365" captionStartId="547.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[210,1347,211,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@547.[193,1394,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="547" captionText="FIGURE 365. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus, ventral; C, urosome, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxilla; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.1 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592044/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 365J</figureCitation>
) with 7 setae on arthrite, 1 on each epipodite and basis, 4 on exopod, and 3 on endopod; endopod incompletely defined from basis; coxal endite absent. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FC20F925FB8BF8C7" box="[997,1102,1771,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 365" captionStartId="547.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[210,1347,211,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-18@547.[193,1394,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="547" captionText="FIGURE 365. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, habitus, ventral; C, urosome, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxilla; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, 0.1 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592044/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 365I</figureCitation>
) 3-segmented; syncoxawith 3, 2, and 2 setae on first to third endites, respectively; basis with claw plus 1 seta; endopod unsegmented with 4 setae. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FC71F89CFBEDF8AD" box="[948,1064,1873,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 366" captionStartId="548.[136,245,683,709]" captionTargetBox="[165,1436,244,614]" captionTargetId="figure-21@548.[136,1451,226,626]" captionTargetPageId="548" captionText="FIGURE 366. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, maxilliped; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 3. Scale bars: 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592046/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 366A</figureCitation>
) as small lobe armed with 6 naked setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED733811FC9AF858FDC6FCAE" blockId="546.[810,1452,275,2070]" lastBlockId="548.[136,778,785,1117]" lastPageId="548" lastPageNumber="549" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">
Legs 1–3 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED733817FBC5F858FBB0F870" box="[1024,1141,1942,1969]" captionStart="FIGURE 366" captionStartId="548.[136,245,683,709]" captionTargetBox="[165,1436,244,614]" captionTargetId="figure-21@548.[136,1451,226,626]" captionTargetPageId="548" captionText="FIGURE 366. Demoixys depressa sp. nov., female. A, maxilliped; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 3. Scale bars: 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592046/files/figure.png" pageId="546" pageNumber="547">Fig. 366</figureCitation>
B–D) rudimentary, each represented by 2 unsegmented lobes; coxa and basis not defined. Leg 1 with 9 setae on exopodal lobe and 4 on endopodal lobe. Leg 2 with 7 setae on exopodal lobe and unarmed endopod. Leg 3 with 4 setae on exopodal lobe and 2 setae on endopodal lobe. Setae on legs 1–3 small or rudimentary. Legs 4 and 5 absent.
</paragraph>
